        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="aFH13Z0y3_51-6DbyUjy-2" parent="1" style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;align=left;verticalAlign=top;spacingLeft=8;fontSize=11;arcSize=0;" value="&lt;b&gt;1. prepare_news&lt;/b&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;b&gt;No LLM&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="61" width="160" x="8560" y="-525" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="aFH13Z0y3_51-6DbyUjy-3" parent="1" style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;align=left;verticalAlign=top;spacingLeft=8;fontSize=11;arcSize=0;" value="&lt;b&gt;2. cluster_news&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0);&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;LLM&lt;/b&gt;: generate labels → merge → assign&lt;/font&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;Generat&lt;font&gt;e:&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;font&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: Lato, &amp;quot;Helvetica Neue&amp;quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);&quot;&gt;Propose new topic names for the batch (not pick from a fixed list). Prompt says reuse existing labels if provided (usually not in first pass). Must consider table data when generating labels.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;Merge:&lt;/b&gt; collapses synonymous labels into one cluster name.&lt;br&gt;&lt;font&gt;&lt;b style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Assign:&lt;/b&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: Lato, &amp;quot;Helvetica Neue&amp;quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);&quot;&gt;Pick exactly one label from the list (no new labels). If ambiguous, pick most specific.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/font&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="171.75" width="310" x="8485" y="-440" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="aFH13Z0y3_51-6DbyUjy-4" parent="1" style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;align=left;verticalAlign=top;spacingLeft=8;fontSize=11;arcSize=0;fontColor=#000000;" value="&lt;b&gt;3. extract_tables&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0);&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;LLM&lt;/b&gt;: schema infer →&amp;nbsp;schema fit →&amp;nbsp;row extract&lt;/font&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;Schema infer:&lt;/b&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: Lato, &amp;quot;Helvetica Neue&amp;quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);&quot;&gt;Full OLAP design from one table: decompose composite headers (e.g. &quot;UAH 3m&quot; → currency + term), separate facts for different metric natures, one main дата/date temporal dim, native-language snake_case names, filter junk values&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;Schema fit:&lt;/b&gt; LLM decides if article fits existing subcluster (header overlap may skip call).&lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;Extract:&lt;/b&gt;&amp;nbsp;Map every table row to normalized OLAP records: decompose composite headers, numeric facts as numbers, null for missing/placeholders, dimension values in original language." vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="201" width="315" x="8482.5" y="-224" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="aFH13Z0y3_51-6DbyUjy-5" parent="1" style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;align=left;verticalAlign=top;spacingLeft=8;fontSize=11;arcSize=0;" value="&lt;b&gt;4. chart_configs&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0);&quot;&gt;&lt;font&gt;&lt;b&gt;LLM&lt;/b&gt;: generate chart UI config&lt;/font&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;Generate chart config&lt;/b&gt;: Chooses UI layout: chart type (may override rule suggestion with justification), aggregation for multi-row vs per-article points, filter widgets." vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="110" width="310" x="8485" y="40" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
